dct_title_s: Taito, Formosa, Taito-cho, Taito-gun. A.M.S. L991
dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Taito. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by form lines and spot elevations. Compiled in 1945 from aerial photgraphy dated September and October 1944, by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, Sheet 2315-III (1944). Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to T'ai-tung [Taitung]. Inset map shows air field near Sakura [Pinlang] (1:25,000). In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Military grid. "Relief shown by form lines. Heights in meters." Three classes of roads or tracks, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. "Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system." Includes "Glossary." Marginal maps and diagrams: Index to boundaries.--Coverage diagram. Inset map shows air field near Sakura [Pinlang] (1:25,000). AMS 1. West Decimal Degree 121.066667. East Decimal Degree 121.150000. South Decimal Degree 22.733333. North Decimal Degree 22.800000.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : U.S. Army Map Service, 1945.
Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
